  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Create awareness of the services offered by the SKMH to encourage referrals ( particularly of difficult cases) by other hospital, surgeons, line agencies, NGO’s and health services providers.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tExpand the treatment of burns to include the whole spectrum of burns, post-burns contracture and defect wounds.\r\n\r\n\r\n\t \r\n\r\n\t\r\n\t\tConducts burn prevention campaigns.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tRaise awareness of burns, the risks to women and children from cooking fires and kerosene stoves and how to prevent/ treat burns and expand the activities in this area to reduce the risks.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tExpand fee-based cosmetic surgery services (not to exceed more than 10% of the total plastic, reconstructive and general surgery services) to generate more income to cover hospital-running expenses.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tExpand fee-based emergency services for tourists (not to exceed more than 10% of the total of total plastic, reconstructive and general surgery services to generate more income to cover hospital - running expenses.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFormulate a human resource development plan including internal and external training and career opportunities.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFormulate a Gender Equity Policy."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
